    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-3648583">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-3648583">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3648583)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3648583">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="3122708"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1512792234 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Dec 2017 04:03</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3648583">
									

<p>None of this read as particularly depressing to me, but I might have a weird scale of depressing. The bit about paranoia resonated with me for 'reasons'.</p>
<p>You are basically using this particular chapter as your blog; that being said, everything we write is basically just blogging. The only real difference is 1) How much effort we put into distancing what we write from ourselves, and 2) How much effort we put into polishing what we write for others to consume. You're not doing much of 1), but you're doing a lot of 2).</p>
<p>I don't know. On one hand I don't want this wiki to just be a collection of our blogs; on the other hand, it takes a lot of guts to just throw all of this stuff out into the air. That being said: There's plenty of room on the scp-wiki, and I don't see why there shouldn't be room for something like this.</p>
<p>I might feel differently if you were not a well-polished writer. That actually makes me feel a little ashamed of myself; it sounds weird to say, but there's a certain privilege to being able to express yourself clearly and concisely in <em>any</em> format.</p>

							</div>

								
					
